The paper discusses methods for connecting visual and textual modalities, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses memory-augmented and modular architectures, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of structured knowledge bases, which is relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR).
